  <p><span class="bold underline">How does ELO Kitty know what's a cat and what's not?</span></p>
  <p>It doesn't. Google does. <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/google-offers-computer-vision-tech-2015-12">AI can now identify objects in images.</a> It's very cool technology. However, it's not perfect, so you may well submit a photo of a cat and Google will tell you it's not. If that happens, try another photo. I'd love to be the arbiter, but don't have time to police images of cats.</p>  
